  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Project Scope**\n\nOkay, I\'m now zeroing in on the project. I\'m focusing on the user\'s need: a mobile bulletin tool for a youth ministry, specifically the role and function requested: a warm and trendy pastor. I\'m prioritizing the user\'s role and requested product for the next phase.\n\n\n**Outlining the Core Features**\n\nI\'m now nailing down the essential features. I\'ve sketched out the structure: a vibrant opening, an order of worship with customizable praise and key elements, and announcements styled for quick consumption. I\'m also including a pre-worship checklist and focusing on design for mobile, aiming for concise text, good spacing, and some design tips. I\'m taking the opportunity to mention Miricanvas and Canva!\n\n\n**Conceptualizing the Application**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the scope: building a \"Mobile Bulletin Customizer & Previewer\" web app. I\'m prioritizing direct user needs, focusing on a high-fidelity mobile mockup. The application will allow users to edit bulletin details within an intuitive sidebar, incorporating a preview with features for customization. The goal is to provide a seamless user experience for creating mobile bulletins. I am now conceptualizing the design for the editing sidebar for preview and editing.\n\n\n**Adding Key Features**\n\nI am now adding key features! I\'ve incorporated a \"Design Guide\" with concept suggestions and real examples, plus the ability to copy the formatted text directly for KakaoTalk or text messages! I\'m particularly excited about the interactive design concept presets - changing the color scheme, fonts, and background in real-time. I\'ve also done a skill check and determined that cloud SQL, firebase, focus mode, and the Gemini API are not needed at this time!\n\n\n**Prioritizing Implementation Accuracy**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the core features, as suggested. I\'m focusing on flawless implementation and setting aside pastor greetings for a future phase. I\'ve reviewed the project\'s metadata; now I need to set a descriptive name for it based on the contents! I am focusing on this first!\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 296873835
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
