    thinking: "**Configuring Descriptive Metadata**\n\nI\'m now diving into `metadata.json` to set up the descriptive name \"\353\252\250\353\260\224\354\235\274 \354\243\274\353\263\264 \354\236\221\354\204\261\352\270\260\" and craft a fitting description: \"\354\262\255\354\206\214\353\205\204/\354\262\255\353\205\204\353\266\200\353\245\274 \354\234\204\355\225\234 \352\260\220\352\260\201\354\240\201\354\235\264\352\263\240 \355\216\270\353\246\254\355\225\234 \353\252\250\353\260\224\354\235\274 \354\243\274\353\263\264 \355\216\270\354\247\221\352\270\260 & Canva \353\224\224\354\236\220\354\235\270 \352\260\200\354\235\264\353\223\234.\" Since this is our inaugural modification, I will record these changes, ensuring a clear and organized record of our actions.\n\n\n**Defining App Components**\n\nI\'ve sketched out the initial app components. I envision a dual-panel setup: a left panel for configuration with sleek controls for bulletin customization, and a center panel showcasing a high-fidelity mobile preview that dynamically updates. I also plan to include design guidance in the form of a right panel to help users with design choices. Now, I\'m working to make this application beautiful.\n\n\n"
