  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Default Presets**\n\nI\'m now focusing on designing and defining default presets and themes. Specifically, I\'m exploring themes that resonate with a young adult/youth church context. \"Warm & Cozy\" is the first concept, featuring pastel, warm neutral shades like cream and peach/beige to evoke a comfortable, cafe-like atmosphere. The main color will be a cream shade (#FFF8E7).\n\n\n**Creating Theme Definitions**\n\nI\'ve been fleshing out more themes to serve as presets. \"Warm & Cozy\" is progressing; I\'ve decided on cream (#FFF8E7) for the main color, with warm apricot (#FFB085) or peach (#E07A5F) as a secondary accent, paired with a serif/sans font mix. \"Modern Mint & Slate\" will be next, with a slate white (#F8FAFC) base and a clean teal or mint (#2DD4BF / #0F766E) accent, using a neo-grotesque font. Then, I\'ll define \"Deep Spiritual Night,\" leaning into midnight indigo (#0F172A), a soft amber/sky blue accent, and minimalist mono fonts. I\'ll place these definitions in `/src/presets.ts`.\n\n\n**Generating Default Data**\n\nI\'m now creating default data for Korean youth services. I\'m focusing on \"Greeting Presets\" for pastors, including options like \"\355\225\234 \354\243\274 \353\217\231\354\225\210 \352\263\240\354\203\235 \353\247\216\354\225\230\354\226\264, \353\202\264\354\235\274 \353\247\214\353\202\230\354\236\220! \360\237\221\213\" and others, with comforting and welcoming messages. I\'m also preparing a \"Default Worship Order,\" planning to pre-fill it with praise track titles and structures to ensure a beautiful and heart-touching start for the youth service. I\'m aiming for data that resonates deeply.\n\n\n**Populating Service Data**\n\nI\'m currently populating service data, specifically for Korean youth services. I\'m detailing the worship order with praise song titles like \"The Spirit Has Come\" and \"Here I Am to Worship.\" I\'m also including representative prayers led by \353\260\225\354\247\200\353\257\274 \354\210\234\354\236\245 (Youth Leader) and bible verses, for example Romans 12:1-2, and sermon details such as \"The Good Thoughts of God\" by Pastor Lee. I\'ve also added example decision texts. Finally, I am including default announcement templates for summer retreats.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 26
      nanos: 525439919
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
