  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the UI Elements**\n\nOkay, I\'m diving into crafting `WorshipForm.tsx`. I\'ve started enumerating the necessary fields, beginning with the greeting selector that will be using preset templates. I am meticulously considering the initial requirements of the left panel\'s form.\n\n\n**Enumerating Key Form Fields**\n\nI\'ve outlined the major components needed for the WorshipForm: greeting (selector, title, message), praise (song list), worship details (prayer leader, bible verse, sermon info, decision text), announcements (editable list with title, description, tags, delete), and a checklist section. Finally, there is the crucial \"Copy for KakaoTalk\" button. I am starting to generate a structured, emoji-filled KakaoTalk message block.\n\n\n**Structuring the Worship Data**\n\nI\'m now focusing on structuring the core worship elements. I\'ve broken down the praise songs, prayer details, announcements, scripture reading, offering, sermon information, and the \"decision\" point into discrete, identifiable components. I\'m also planning to represent the announcements as an editable list with title, description, and tags for each entry. Finally, I\'ve got to consider how to represent the pre-worship checklist and include the end message.\n\n\n"
