  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Adding Bold Typography**\n\nOkay, I\'m now adding the \"Bold Typography\" design theme to `/src/presets.ts`. First, I\'m configuring the design theme within the file.\n\n\n**Defining Bold Typography Theme**\n\nI\'m now integrating the \"\353\263\274\353\223\234 \355\203\200\354\235\264\355\217\254 & \354\264\210\353\241\235 \352\260\220\354\204\261 (Bold Sage)\" theme. I\'ve captured its core concept, translating \"\353\224\260\353\234\273\355\225\234 \354\235\274\354\203\201\354\235\230 \352\270\260\353\241\235\" into a natural, refined aesthetic. I\'ve established the background and text colors, along with accent and card backgrounds, focusing on the warm chocolate brown and sage green. I\'ve also identified and implemented the `font-playfair` tailwind class for the Playfair Display font.\n\n\n**Structuring Color Definitions**\n\nI\'m now structuring the color definitions for the \"Bold Sage\" theme in `/src/presets.ts`. I\'ve created an array to hold the color data, including names, hex codes, Tailwind classes, and descriptions for each color: natural ivory, sage green, chocolate brown, and natural ginger skin. I\'m focusing on ensuring proper organization of this data within the existing theme structure. I\'m inserting this theme at the 0 index of `DESIGN_THEMES`.\n\n\n**Implementing Default Theme**\n\nI\'ve decided to make the new \"Bold Sage\" theme the default. Its definition is now ready, and I\'m configuring it as the first item, meaning it will load immediately upon startup. I\'ve defined its `id`, `name`, `description`, and `concept`, along with colors for `bgColor`, `textColor`, `accentBg`, `accentText`, `cardBg`, and `borderColor`, and have successfully set its `fontFamily` using the `font-[Playfair_Display]` class.\n\n\n**Refining Typography Choices**\n\nI\'m now refining the typography for the \"Bold Sage\" theme, adding further definition to the font specifics. The theme will use \"\355\224\214\353\240\210\354\235\264\355\216\230\354\226\264 & \353\205\270\355\206\240\354\202\260\354\212\244 (Playfair & Noto Sans)\" with the tagline \"\353\224\260\354\212\244\355\225\234 \354\230\250\352\270\260\354\231\200 \354\247\200\353\251\264 \353\247\244\352\261\260\354\247\204\354\235\230 \354\227\254\353\260\261.\" Playfair Display (Italic) will be used for large headings and English slogans, and Noto Sans KR for the Korean body text. I\'ve also incorporated a refined color palette, including natural ivory, sage green, cacao deep brown, and natural ginger skin.\n\n\n**Adjusting Greeting Content**\n\nI\'m now focusing on adjusting the preset greeting content. I\'ll replace the existing first greeting to match the new, immersive text: \"\354\225\210\353\205\225, \354\262\255\353\205\204\353\266\200 \354\271\234\352\265\254\353\223\244! :) \354\204\244\353\240\210\353\212\224 \355\206\240\354\232\224\354\235\274 \353\260\244\354\235\264\354\225\274. \353\202\264\354\235\274 \354\232\260\353\246\254\352\260\200 \355\225\250\352\273\230 \353\252\250\354\227\254 \353\223\234\353\246\264 \354\230\210\353\260\260\353\245\274 \352\270\260\353\214\200\355\225\230\353\251\260, \353\257\270\353\246\254 \354\243\274\353\263\264\353\245\274 \353\263\264\353\202\264\354\244\204\352\262\214. \353\224\260\353\234\273\355\225\234 \353\247\210\354\235\214\354\234\274\353\241\234 \353\202\264\354\235\274 \353\247\214\353\202\230\354\236\220!\" I\'m ensuring the \"Hello, Sunday!\" greeting title or \"Hello, Sunday! \342\234\250\" remains appropriate. I\'ll also add \"Way Maker\" and \"\354\243\274\353\245\274 \354\234\204\355\225\234 \353\205\270\353\236\230\" as preset praise songs.\n\n\n"
